    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "D&C",
        "delineation": "Section",
        "number": 131,
        "summary": "1\u20134, Celestial marriage is essential to exaltation in the highest heaven; 5\u20136, How men are sealed up unto eternal life is explained; 7\u20138, All spirit is matter.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "In the celestial glory there are three heavens or degrees;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:70. TG\u00a0Celestial Glory.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heaven. BD\u00a0Heaven.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And in order to obtain the highest, a man must enter into this order of the priesthood [meaning the new and everlasting covenant of marriage];",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 132:21 (5\u201321). TG\u00a0Family, Eternal; Man, Potential to Become like Heavenly Father.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Genealogy and Temple Work.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood, Melchizedek.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0New and Everlasting Covenant.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 128
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Celestial.",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 140
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And if he does not, he cannot obtain it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He may enter into the other, but that is the end of his kingdom; he cannot have an increase.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 22:30 (23\u201333); D&C 132:16\u201317. TG\u00a0Marriage, Fatherhood; Marriage, Motherhood.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "(May 17th, 1843.) The more sure word of prophecy means a man's knowing that he is sealed up unto eternal life, by revelation and the spirit of prophecy, through the power of the Holy Priesthood.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Pet. 1:19 (3\u201321). TG\u00a0Prophecy.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Election; Eternal Life; Sealing.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 68:12; 88:4.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It is impossible for a man to be saved in ignorance.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mal. 2:7 (7\u20139); D&C 90:15 (14\u201315); 107:99 (99\u2013100). TG\u00a0Apathy; Education; Ignorance; Knowledge; Learn.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There is no such thing as immaterial matter. All spirit is matter, but it is more fine or pure, and can only be discerned by purer eyes;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Spirit Body; Spirit Creation.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:12; 97:16; Moses 1:11.",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We cannot see it; but when our bodies are purified we shall see that it is all matter.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 129:8.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 77:2; Moses 3:5 (5\u20139).",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}